assistant_prompt:
es this code below but I get multiple lines of query strings & I can't get the last query string in each line.

A:

You can use this regex to match a query string:
(?<=?)(?:\?\?.*)

Explanation:
(?<=?)(?:\?\?.*) - check if there is a query string before the first ?
(?:\?\?.*) - optionally match any query string after ?.

You can save it in a variable:
$queryString = "(?<=?)(?:\?\?.*)";

And then match every line in the log file:
$lines = @file('logFile.txt');

foreach ($lines as $line) {
    if ($line -match $queryString) {
        # do whatever you want here with $line
    }
}

