assistant_prompt:
I have a problem, I have to write my own code for a text editor, I have to do this without using external libraries, I have done it, but I have to pass an argument to the user, so he can choose a path, to save the file, I have to use std::string, and I have to make a function to save the file, I have to return the path to the file, but I have a problem with that, I have not been able to make the function, so I was able to write my own code, but I have not been able to make a function to get the path, I have tried to use a stringstream, but not found the way to do it, and I have tried with a vector, but I do not know how to do it, can anyone help me please?

A:

I would use a stringstream to get the path to the file.
You can use the >> operator to retrieve the data from the stringstream:
std::stringstream ss;
ss << "C:/path/to/the/file" ;
std::string path = ss.str();

Alternatively, if you want to save the path as a std::string, you can use the stringstream::str method:
std::string path = ss.str();
std::string file_path = path + "/fileName";

A:

You don't need a stringstream.
You can use the following line to get the path of the file:
boost::filesystem::path path = boost::filesystem::current_path() / "/fileName";

You should use std::stringstream instead of boost::filesystem::path to save the path.

